headline: Norwegian Cruise Line misses quarterly estimates on weaker demand for premium voyages
summary: Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings missed first-quarter revenue and profit estimates on Wednesday, as rising concerns about tariff uncertainty have pressured demand for the cruise operator's premium sea voyages. Shares of the company were down 7% in premarket trading. After benefiting from a post-pandemic surge, Norwegian Cruise has seen a slowdown in new bookings as consumers shy away from its high-end cruises and private island getaways amid looming concerns about a potential recession.
